HEADWORD: etched
<hw>etched</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Cut or impressed into a
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> engraved, graven, incised.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Corroded so that the surface is matte and not fully
transparent; -- of glass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etcher</ent>⟦br⟧
